<paragraph id="C10CC2073C21FFFEFFC9789A599EA101" blockId="1.[94,643,1688,1872]" lastBlockId="1.[680,1229,184,336]" pageId="1">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFFC9789A5ABFA6FE" box="[94,194,1689,1712]" italics="true" pageId="1">Discussão:</emphasis>
Dentre as espécies unicolores do gênero 
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFFC978BB5B03A69E" authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[94,382,1720,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFFC978BB5ABBA69E" box="[94,198,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="1">Periboeum</emphasis>
Thomson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
, com rugas no pronoto, espinho externo nas extremidades elitrais e fêmures e tíbias unicolores, 
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFEBE78FB5B8EA75E" authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2010" box="[297,499,1784,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFEBE78FB5B8EA75E" box="[297,499,1784,1808]" italics="true" pageId="1">Periboeum spinosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E8F4A36E3C21FFFEFE6B78FB5831A741" box="[508,588,1784,1807]" pageId="1" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
assemelha-se a 
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFF41791A5B8CA77E" authority="(Perroud, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Perroud" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[214,497,1816,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFF41791A5B3DA77E" box="[214,320,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1">P. vicinum</emphasis>
(Perroud, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
e 
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFD9A791A5B6DA71E" authority="(Erichson, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piliferum">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFD9A791A58FFA77E" box="[525,642,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="1">P. piliferum</emphasis>
(Erichson, 1847)
</taxonomicName>
. Difere de ambas pelos flagelômeros III-VI com dois espinhos; de 
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFC457EBA5E3CA09E" box="[978,1089,185,208]" italics="true" pageId="1">
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFC457EBA5E40A09E" baseAuthorityName="Perroud" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[978,1085,185,208]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">P. vicinum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
conhecida da 
<collectingCountry id="B9A482973C21FFFEFD3F7EDB5972A0BE" box="[680,783,216,240]" name="Colombia" pageId="1">Colômbia</collectingCountry>
e 
<collectingCountry id="B9A482973C21FFFEFCBF7EDB5901A0BE" box="[808,892,216,240]" name="Panama" pageId="1">Panamá</collectingCountry>
, difere pela ausência de tubérculos no pronoto e pela pontuação densa nos lados do meio. Em 
<taxonomicName id="06B3B9843C21FFFEFC827F1A5903A17E" baseAuthorityName="Perroud" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[789,894,281,304]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Periboeum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinum">
<emphasis id="F3C71E153C21FFFEFC827F1A5903A17E" box="[789,894,281,304]" italics="true" pageId="1">P. vicinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
o pronoto tem cinco tubérculos e a pontuação é muito esparsa.
</paragraph>
